cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper is about visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a deep learning framework, which involves training a Siamese network, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of adaptive tracking, which involves making decisions based on changing conditions, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category. The paper also evaluates its proposed framework on several benchmark datasets, which are commonly used in multimedia research, so cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category. Finally, the paper's focus on tracking moving objects suggests that it could also be relevant to cs.RO (Robotics).
